    :Section Link Private function    ‚ćĚ to avoid clobber auto-complete in ‚éēSE.Link

    ‚ąá src‚ÜźGetRefSource ns;file
      :If ~0‚ąä‚ćīfile‚Üź# CurrentFileName ns  ‚ćĚ TODO Mantis this - ‚éēSRC won't provide :Require headers if they exist
      :AndIf ~0‚ąä‚ćīsrc‚ÜźGetFileSource file  ‚ćĚ source accessible
          :Return
     
      :EndIf
      :Trap 16 22 ‚čĄ src‚Üź‚éēSRC ns   ‚ćĚ scripted namespace
      :Case 22 ‚čĄ src‚Üź'Cannot get source of ',(‚ćēns),': File not found: ',# CurrentFileName ns ‚ćĚ v18.1 throws a FILE NAME ERROR if file not found - whereas v18.0 throws a NONCE ERROR
      :Else
          :If ~0‚ąä‚ćīfile‚Üź# CurrentFileName ns ‚ćĚ source not available anymore - cannot be an unscripted namespace (‚éēSRC should really set ‚éēDMX.ENX)
              src‚Üź'Cannot get source of ',(‚ćēns),': File not found: ',file
          :Else ‚čĄ src‚Üź‚éēNULL                 ‚ćĚ unscripted namespace
          :EndIf
      :EndTrap
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá sub‚ÜźSubExt val;cr;lf;Char;crs;lfs;lss
    ‚ćĚ Takes an array value, then returns the appropriate sub-extension (incl. leading ".") for its source file
      (cr lf)‚Üź‚éēUCS 13 10
      ‚ćĚ Compatible line breaks: LF VT FF CR NEL  LS   PS
      lss‚Üź‚éēUCS ‚éēAVU‚ą©‚ć£(82=‚éēDR'')‚äĘ10 11 12 13 133 8232 8233
      Char‚Üź‚éēDR‚ąä80 82 160 320‚ć®
     
      :If 1=‚Č°val ‚ćĚ simple
      :AndIf 2=‚ČĘ‚ćīval ‚ćĚ matrix
      :AndIf Char val
      :AndIf 0‚Č†‚ČĘval ‚ćĚ with rows
      :AndIf ' '‚ą®.‚Č†‚äĘ/val ‚ćĚ some of which have non-space in last column
      :AndIf ~lss(‚ą®/‚ąä)val ‚ćĚ without line seps
          sub‚Üź'.mat'
     
      :ElseIf 1=‚Č°val ‚ćĚ simple
      :AndIf 1=‚ČĘ‚ćīval ‚ćĚ vector
      :AndIf Char val
      :AndIf cr lf‚ąä‚ć®‚äÉ‚ĆĹval ‚ćĚ ending with CR or LF
          crs‚Üźcr=val
          lfs‚Üźlf=val
      :AndIf (~‚ą®/crs)‚ą®(~‚ą®/lfs)‚ą®(0,crs)‚Č°(lfs,0) ‚ćĚ only LF or only CR or only CRLF
      :AndIf ~(lss~cr lf)(‚ą®/‚ąä)val ‚ćĚ with no other line seps
          sub‚Üź'.','CRLF'/‚ć®2/‚ą®/¬®crs lfs
     
      :ElseIf 2=‚Č°val ‚ćĚ even-nested
      :AndIf 1=‚ČĘ‚ćīval ‚ćĚ vector
      :AndIf 1‚ąß.=(‚ČĘ‚ćī)¬®val ‚ćĚ of vectors
      :AndIf ‚ąß/Char¬®val
      :AndIf ~‚ą®/lss‚ąė(‚ą®/‚ąä)¬®val ‚ćĚ without line seps
          sub‚Üź'.vec'
     
      :Else
          sub‚Üź'' ‚ćĚ APLAN
      :EndIf
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá src‚Üź{ns}GetAplSource name_opts;nc;Cut;val;sub;name;opts
    ‚ćĚ if OK src is a vector of text vectors, unless unscripted namespace with get ‚éēNULL
    ‚ćĚ if failed, src is a text vector holding the error message
    ‚ćĚ name may be empty to get the source of ns
      name_opts‚Üź‚äÜname_opts
      (name opts)‚Üźname_opts,DefaultOpts‚ć£(1=‚ČĘname_opts)‚äĘ‚ć¨
     
      :If 0‚ąä‚ćīname
          src‚ÜźGetRefSource ns
      :Else
          :If 900‚Ć∂‚ć¨ ‚čĄ ns‚Üź‚éēNS ‚ć¨ ‚čĄ :EndIf
          nc‚Üź|ns NameClass name
          :Select nc
          :Case 2.1 ‚ćĚ variable
              val‚Üźns‚ćéname ‚ćĚ what if the var already has a file
              :If opts.text‚Č°'aplan'
                  sub‚Üź''
              :Else
                  sub‚ÜźSubExt val
                  Cut‚Üź{lb‚Üź‚éēUCS ‚ćļ ‚čĄ t‚Üźlb,‚ćĶ ‚čĄ (‚ČĘ‚ćļ)‚Üď¬®t‚äā‚ć®lb‚ć∑t}
              :EndIf
              :Select sub ‚ćĚ simple
              :Case '.mat'
                  src‚Üź‚Üďval
              :Case '.LF'
                  src‚Üź10 Cut val
              :Case '.CRLF'
                  src‚Üź13 10 Cut val
              :Case '.CR'
                  src‚Üź13 Cut val
              :Case '.vec'
                  src‚Üźval ‚čĄ :Return ‚ćĚ skip emptiness test
              :Else
                  :Trap 0 ‚čĄ src‚Üź‚éēSE.Dyalog.Array.Serialise val
                  :Else ‚čĄ src‚Üź'Cannot get source of ',(‚ćēns),'.',name,': Array cannot be serialised'
                  :EndTrap
              :EndSelect
          :CaseList 3.1 3.2 4.1 4.2 ‚ćĚ tradfn/dfn/tradop/dop - v18.0 cannot get source of functions "as typed"
              src‚Üź‚éēNULL
              :If IS181
                  :Select a‚Üź##.ALWAYSREFORMAT
                  :CaseList 0 1
                      :Trap 11
                          src‚Üź(SRC_BEST SRC_NORMALIZED)[1+a]ns.‚éēATX name
                      :EndTrap
                  :Case 2
                      src‚Üźns.‚éēNR name
                  :EndSelect
              :EndIf ‚ćĚ ‚éēATX returns ‚éēNULL if source not available - ‚éēATX errors if name doesn't exist
              :If src‚Č°‚éēNULL ‚čĄ src‚Üźns.‚éēNR name ‚čĄ :EndIf  ‚ćĚ de-tokenised source - not "as typed" - ‚éēNR never errors
          :CaseList 9.1 9.4 9.5 ‚čĄ src‚ÜźGetRefSource ns‚ćéname ‚ćĚ ns/class/interface
          :Else ‚čĄ src‚Üź'Cannot get source of ',(‚ćēns),'.',name,': Invalid name class (',(‚ćēnc),')'
          :EndSelect
      :EndIf
      :If 0‚ąä‚ćīsrc ‚čĄ src‚Üź'Cannot get source of ',(‚ćēns),'.',name ‚čĄ :EndIf
    ‚ąá
    ‚ąá src‚ÜźGetFileSource file;type
      src‚Üź‚ć¨  ‚ćĚ ‚ć¨ means failure to read file - empty file produces 0‚ćī‚äā''
      :Trap 0
          :If 1=type‚Üź1 ‚éēNINFO file ‚čĄ src‚Üź‚éēNULL  ‚ćĚ directory ‚Üí namespace
          :ElseIf 2=type ‚čĄ src‚ÜźGetFile file     ‚ćĚ file
          :EndIf
      :Else
          Warn'Unable to read "',file,'": ',‚éēDMX.Message
      :EndTrap
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá has‚ÜźHasRequire src;line;patt;req
    ‚ćĚ does script have :Require statements ?
      :If has‚Üźsrc‚ČĘ‚éēNULL
      :AndIf has‚Üź~0‚ąä‚ćīreq‚Üź‚éēIO+'^\s*:require\s+' '^\s*(‚ćĚ.*)?$'‚éēS 2 3‚ć†'IC' 1‚äĘsrc  ‚ćĚ lines startting with ':Require ' and empty lines
      :AndIf has‚Üź1‚ąä2‚äÉ(line patt)‚Üź‚Üď‚ćČ‚ÜĎreq   ‚ćĚ just because ‚Üď‚ćČ‚ÜĎ won't work on empty ‚éēS, which yields ‚äā‚ć¨
          has‚Üź1‚ąä((‚ć≥‚ćīline)=line[‚ćčline])/patt  ‚ćĚ found at top of script (consecutive row of empty lines and :Require's
      :EndIf
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá (name nc)‚Üź{where}Fix(name src force);FIX;file;invalid;monitor;names;nc;stops;trace;unnamed;Set;With;at;modTime;owner
    ‚ćĚ Fix source and return names and nameclass
    ‚ćĚ src may be actual source (‚éēNULL or vector of strings) or file name (string)
    ‚ćĚ nameclass is 0 if no valid source was found, ¬Į1 if name is invalid, ¬Į9.1 if unscripted namespace
      :If 900‚Ć∂‚ć¨ ‚čĄ where‚Üź‚éēDMX.(‚éēNS ‚ć¨) ‚čĄ :EndIf  ‚ćĚ fix in dummy namespace that cannot break anything (e.g. ':Namespace' '##.‚éēIO‚Üź0' ':EndNamespace')
      :If src‚Č°‚ć¨ ‚čĄ name‚Üź'' ‚čĄ nc‚Üź0 ‚čĄ :Return ‚čĄ :EndIf  ‚ćĚ file not accessible
      :If 1=‚Č°src ‚čĄ src‚Üź'file://',file‚Üźsrc ‚čĄ :Else ‚čĄ file‚Üź'' ‚čĄ :EndIf ‚ćĚ file name given instead of source
      :If ~IS181 ‚čĄ FIX‚Üźwhere.‚éēFIX ‚čĄ :Else
          ‚ćĚ Quiet            0|1     (default 0)   ‚ćĚ do not output status messages - link issue #149
          ‚ćĚ AllowLateBinding 0|1     (default 1)   ‚ćĚ allow missing dependencies
          ‚ćĚ FixWithErrors    0|1|2   (default 0,2=prompt)  ‚ćĚ allow errors in script - link issue #144
          ‚ćĚ Link             0|1     (default 1)   ‚ćĚ maintain the link to the file - link issue #155
          FIX‚Üźwhere.‚éēFIX‚ć†('Quiet' 1)('AllowLateBinding' 1)('FixWithErrors'force)('Link'(~0‚ąä‚ćīfile))
      :EndIf
      ‚ćĚ:If (‚Ćä|where.‚éēNC‚äāname)‚ąä3 4 ‚čĄ (stops trace monitor)‚Üź(where.‚éēSTOP name)(where.‚éēTRACE name)(‚ä£/where.‚éēMONITOR name)  ‚ćĚ link issue #148 and #129
      ‚ćĚ:Else ‚čĄ stops‚Üźtrace‚Üźmonitor‚Üź‚ć¨
      ‚ćĚ:EndIf
      ‚ćĚ attempt to fix as named script because this is the most commonly expected format
      :Trap 0 ‚čĄ names‚Üź(2 FIX src)  ‚ćĚ fn/op/script - can work from file
      :Else ‚čĄ names‚Üź0‚ćī‚äā''
      :EndTrap
      :If ~0‚ąä‚ćīnames  ‚ćĚ fix succeeded - this is the only case where actual apl name may be different from what was expected
          :If 1=‚ČĘnames ‚čĄ name‚Üź‚äÉnames ‚čĄ nc‚Üźwhere.‚éēNC‚äāname
          :Else ‚čĄ name‚Üź'' ‚čĄ nc‚Üź0  ‚ćĚ multiple names in single file not supported
          :EndIf
          :If ‚éēNEXISTS file
              (modTime owner)‚Üź3 5 ‚éēNINFO file
              modTime[7]‚Üź0           ‚ćĚ 0 ms
              owner‚Üź2‚äÉ‚éēNPARTS owner  ‚ćĚ remove domain: foo/bar ‚Üí bar; bar ‚Üí bar
            ‚ćĚ ‚ĒĆ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄset attribs to‚ĒÄ‚Ēź‚ĒĆ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄupdated‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚Ēź‚ĒĆ‚ĒÄold attribs‚ĒÄ‚Ēź
              name where.(1159‚Ć∂)‚ć®modTime owner@2 4 where.‚éēAT name
          :EndIf
          ‚ćĚ:If ((‚Ćä|nc)‚ąä3 4)‚ąß(0‚ą®.<‚äÉ‚ąė‚ćī¬®stops trace monitor)  ‚ćĚ restore stops, traces and monitor - monitor timing information will be lost
          ‚ćĚ    stops where.‚éēSTOP name ‚čĄ trace where.‚éēTRACE name ‚čĄ monitor where.‚éēMONITOR name
          ‚ćĚ:EndIf
          :Return  ‚ćĚ named script fixed
      :EndIf
      ‚ćĚrequired‚Üź11 116‚Č°‚éēDMX.(EN ENX)  ‚ćĚ 2 ‚éēFIX failed because cannot read :Required file
      unnamed‚Üź11 121‚Č°‚éēDMX.(EN ENX)  ‚ćĚ 2 ‚éēFIX failed because script was unnamed
      ‚ćĚnoaccess‚Üź19 12‚Č°‚éēDMX.(EN ENX)   ‚ćĚ 2 ‚éēFIX 'file://' on directory
      ‚ćĚnofile‚Üź22 12‚Č°‚éēDMX.(EN ENX)   ‚ćĚ 2 ‚éēFIX 'file://' on missing file
      ‚ćĚnointerface‚Üź11 31‚Č°‚éēDMX.(EN ENX)  ‚ćĚ fixing class with missing interface
      ‚ćĚ name must be valid because we define it in the following code
      :If ¬Į1=where NameClass name ‚čĄ nc‚Üź¬Į1 ‚čĄ :Return ‚čĄ :EndIf
      :If unnamed  ‚ćĚ unnamed script
          name{‚ćé‚ćļ,'‚Üź‚ćĶ'}FIX src  ‚ćĚ can work from file
          nc‚Üźwhere.‚éēNC‚äā,name
          :Return  ‚ćĚ unnamed script fixed
      :EndIf
      ‚ćĚ remaining possibilities are array or trad ns
      :If ~0‚ąä‚ćīfile ‚čĄ src‚ÜźGetFileSource file ‚čĄ :EndIf ‚ćĚ they both require source, not filename
      :If src‚Č°‚ć¨ ‚čĄ name‚Üź'' ‚čĄ nc‚Üź0 ‚čĄ :Return ‚čĄ :EndIf  ‚ćĚ file not accessible
      :If src‚Č°‚éēNULL  ‚ćĚ trad namespace - was not tested before because the 1=1‚éēNINFO would have been costy
          name where.‚éēNS'' ‚čĄ nc‚Üź¬Į9.1
          :Return  ‚ćĚ trad ns created
      :EndIf
      :Trap 0
          Set‚Üźname‚ąėwhere.{‚ćé‚ćļ,'‚Üź‚ćĶ'}
          With‚Üź{‚ąäsrc,¬®‚äā‚éēUCS ‚ćĶ}
          :Select ‚éēC(‚ć≥‚ąė'.'‚Üď‚äĘ)2‚äÉ‚éēNPARTS file ‚ćĚ sub-ext
          :Case '.cr'
              Set With 13
          :Case '.lf'
              Set With 10
          :Case '.crlf'
              Set With 13 10
          :Case '.mat'
              Set‚ÜĎsrc
          :Case '.vec'
              Set src
          :Case ''
              Set where ‚éēSE.Dyalog.Array.Deserialise src
          :Else
              Error'File "',file,'" has invalid sub-extension'
          :EndSelect
          nc‚Üźwhere NameClass name
      :Else
          name‚Üź'' ‚čĄ nc‚Üź0  ‚ćĚ unknown
      :EndTrap
    ‚ąá
    ‚ąá fixed‚Üźtarget QFix(file name tie ignoreErrors ignoreSame);changed;nc;tie;value;fpath;fname;fext;src;With
    ‚ćĚ fixed=1: fixed source
    ‚ćĚ fixed=0: source already up to date - not fixed
    ‚ćĚ fixed=¬Į1: failed to fix source
    ‚ćĚ ignoreErrors: 1 to fix scripts containing errors
    ‚ćĚ ignoreSame  : 1 to refix unchanged source files (used by Resync)
     
      (fpath fname fext)‚Üź‚éēNPARTS file
      :If '.apla'‚Č°‚éēC fext  ‚ćĚ If it is an array, do not try to ‚éēFIX
     
          src‚Üź‚äÉ‚éēNGET file 1
          With‚Üź{‚ąäsrc,¬®‚äā‚éēUCS ‚ćĶ}
          :Select ‚éēC(‚ć≥‚ąė'.'‚Üď‚äĘ)fname ‚ćĚ sub-ext
          :Case 'cr'
              value‚ÜźWith 13
          :Case 'lf'
              value‚ÜźWith 10
          :Case 'crlf'
              value‚ÜźWith 13 10
          :Case 'mat'
              value‚Üź‚ÜĎsrc
          :Case 'vec'
              value‚Üźsrc
          :Case ''
              :Trap 0 ‚ćĚ Trap any failue in Deserialise
                  value‚Üźtarget ‚éēSE.Dyalog.Array.Deserialise src
              :Else
                  fixed‚Üź¬Į1
                  :Return
              :EndTrap
          :Else ‚ćĚ invalid sub-ext
