              :If opts.(singlefile‚ąßcaseCode)
                  opts.dir‚Üź‚äÉfiles ‚ćĚ replace with case coded name
              :EndIf
          :EndIf
          :If ‚ą®/mask‚Üź(inx‚Üź‚ć≥‚ć®0 CaseText files)‚Č†(‚ć≥‚ČĘfiles)
              ‚ćĚ cannot let user do this on any platform - if the directory is moved to windows then the user will be screwed
              Error'File name case clash - try using caseCode‚Üź1:',FmtLines(ns,'.')‚ąė,¬®names[,(mask/inx),[1.5]‚ćłmask]
          :EndIf
          :If overwrite‚Č°0 ‚čĄ :AndIf 1‚ąämask‚Üź‚éēNEXISTS files
              Error'Files already exist: use the -overwrite flag to force overwriting the following files:',FmtLines WinSlash¬®mask/files
          :ElseIf overwrite‚Č°1 ‚čĄ 3 ‚éēNDELETE files
          :EndIf
     
          :If 3=opts.(‚éēNC beforeWrite)  ‚ćĚ user callback on file write
              mask‚Üź(‚ČĘfiles)‚ćī1
              :For i :In ‚ć≥‚ćīfiles
                  mask[i]‚Üź(‚ćéopts.beforeWrite)'beforeWrite'opts(i‚äÉfiles)(ns,'.',i‚äÉnames)(nsref NameClass i‚äÉnames)(ns,'.',i‚äÉnames)(i‚äÉsrc)
              :EndFor
              (files oldfiles names src)/‚ć®‚Üź‚äāmask  ‚ćĚ keep what was not processed by user
          :EndIf
     
          mask‚Üźsrc‚ąä‚éēNULL  ‚ćĚ unscripted namespaces
          (tradnames tradfiles)‚Üźmask‚ąė/¬®(names files)
          (files oldfiles names src)/‚ć®‚Üź‚äā(~mask)
          :If 0‚Č†‚ČĘtradfiles
              3 ‚éēMKDIR¬®tradfiles ‚čĄ mask‚Üź‚éēNEXISTS tradfiles
              written,‚Üźmask/tradfiles ‚čĄ failed,‚Üź(ns,'.')‚ąė,¬®(~mask)/tradnames
          :EndIf
          :If 0‚Č†‚ČĘfiles
              :If 0‚ąämask‚Üź~HasNewlines¬®‚ąä¬®src  ‚ćĚ cannot write newlines
                  failed,‚Üź{ns,'.',‚ćĶ,' (contains newline characters)'}¬®(~mask)/names
                  (files oldfiles names src)/‚ć®‚Üź‚äāmask
              :EndIf
          :AndIf 0‚Č†‚ČĘfiles
              mask‚Üźsrc(nsref Into)¬®files  ‚ćĚ failed to write
              written,‚Üźmask/files ‚čĄ failed,‚Üź(ns,'.')‚ąė,¬®(~mask)/names
              :If ‚ą®/mask‚Üźmask‚ąß(oldfiles‚ČĘ¬®files)‚ąß(0‚Č†‚ČĘ¬®oldfiles)  ‚ćĚ delete oldfilename which was incorrect if write was successful
                  ‚éēNDELETE¬®mask/oldfiles
              :EndIf
          :EndIf
      :EndIf
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá (files isdir ts)‚Üźopts(root ListFiles ts)dir;dirs;hidden;list;mask;order;parts;g
      :If 0=‚éēNC'opts.singlefile' ‚čĄ opts.singlefile‚Üź0 ‚čĄ :EndIf ‚ćĚ /// temporary
      list‚Üź‚ÜĎ(0 1 6,ts/3)‚éēNINFO‚ć†1‚ć†'Recurse' 1‚äĘdir,(~opts.singlefile)/'/*'     ‚ćĚ recursive listing of everything  list[filename type hidden;]
      parts‚Üź‚éēNPARTS¬®list[1;]
      list‚Üźlist[;g‚Üź‚ćč'‚éē'‚Č†‚äÉ¬®list[3;]]                 ‚ćĚ System names first
     
      mask‚Üź1=list[3;]                               ‚ćĚ mask for hidden items
      hidden‚Üźmask/list ‚čĄ list/‚ć®‚Üź~mask               ‚ćĚ crop hidden (files and) folders
      parts‚Üźparts[(~mask)/g]
      hidden‚Üź(1=hidden[2;])/hidden[1;]              ‚ćĚ keep directories only (files have already been removed from list)
      hidden‚Üźhidden,¬®'/'                            ‚ćĚ protect against similarly named files
      hidden,‚Üź('.'=‚äÉ¬®‚ąä¬®1‚Üď¬®parts)/list[1;]           ‚ćĚ files and directories that start with a '.' are considered hidden too
      list/‚ć®‚Üź~‚ą®‚ĆŅhidden‚ąė.Begins list[1;]             ‚ćĚ filter away things that come below hidden directories
     
      dirs‚Üź(1=list[2;])/list                        ‚ćĚ second column has 1 for dirs
      :If root
          dirs,‚ć®‚Üź(-~ts)‚Üďdir 1 0(0 0 0 0 0 0 0)       ‚ćĚ add self with a fake timestamp (dir timestamps are ignored)
      :EndIf
      dirs[1;],‚Üź'/'                                 ‚ćĚ add slash to name
     
      files‚Üź(2=list[2;])/list                       ‚ćĚ second column has 2 for files; first column is filename
      files/‚ć®‚Üźopts HasExtn files[1;]                ‚ćĚ must be of correct extension
     
      list‚Üźfiles,dirs
      ‚ćĚ slashes after all chars and quads before all
      ‚ćĚ in "descending" order into folders:
      ‚ćĚ must process parent folders and all its files (including sysvars) first
      ‚ćĚ we do ‚ÜĎ1+‚éēUCS so that fill item (0) is not the same as have (‚éēUCS 0) in filename (and comes before it)
      order‚Üź‚ćč¬Į2@{0=‚ćĶ}¬Į1@{9109=¬Į1+‚ćĶ}9999999@{47=¬Į1+‚ćĶ}‚ÜĎ1+‚éēUCS¬®list[1;]
      list‚Üźlist[;order]
     
      files‚Üźlist[1;] ‚čĄ isdir‚Üź1=list[2;]
      :If ts ‚čĄ ts‚Üźlist[4;] ‚čĄ :Else ‚čĄ ts‚Üź‚äā‚ć¨ ‚čĄ :EndIf
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá (fixed failed)‚Üźopts FixFiles(target source overwrite);‚éēAVU;FixFile;_;actname;actnames;actnc;actncs;alldirs;allexts;allfiles;allnames;dir;expfiles;expname;expnames;ext;extorder;exts;file;fixedfiles;flatten;fullname;hasnc;hidden;i;inx;lasttodo;list;mask;ncorder;ns;order;parent;parents;quadfile;source;todo;classic;z
    ‚ćĚ Load items from files in folders
    ‚ćĚ overwrite=¬Į1 : empty target - no overwrite
    ‚ćĚ overwrite=0 : non-empty target - no overwrite
    ‚ćĚ overwrite=1 : non-empty target - overwrite
      fixed‚Üźfixedfiles‚Üźfailed‚Üź0‚ćī‚äā''
      :If 1‚Č†1 ‚éēNINFO source ‚čĄ allfiles‚Üź,‚äā,source ‚ćĚ single filename
      :Else ‚čĄ allfiles‚Üź‚äÉopts(1 ListFiles 0)source  ‚ćĚ whole directory including root
      :EndIf
     
      :If classic‚Üź82=‚éēDR'' ‚ćĚ Classic
      :AndIf (‚ČĘallfiles)‚Č•i‚Üź(¬Į10‚ÜĎ¬®allfiles)‚ć≥‚ć•‚éēC‚äā'/‚éēAVU.apla' ‚ćĚ Source contains ‚éēAVU
          :Trap 0 ‚ćĚ Try to set ‚éēAVU so that all ‚éēNGET/‚éēFIX operations will use saved ‚éēAVU
              ‚éēAVU‚Üź(‚ćéopts.ns).‚éēAVU‚Üź‚éēSE.Dyalog.Array.Deserialise‚äÉ‚éēNGET i‚äÉallfiles
          :Else
              Warn'Unable to set ‚éēAVU from ',i‚äÉallfiles
          :EndTrap
      :EndIf
     
      (parents expnames actnames actncs)‚Üźopts DetermineAplName allfiles  ‚ćĚ expected names (one per file), actual names (one list per file), actual name classes (one list per file)
      :If opts.singlefile
      :AndIf actnames‚ČĘexpnames
          :If classic‚ąß0=‚ČĘ‚äÉactnames ‚ćĚ Empty name in Classic?
              :Trap 92 ‚ćĚ TRANSLATION ERROR
                  z‚ÜźGetFile‚äÉallfiles
              :Else
                  Error ‚éēDMX.(EM,' ',Message)
              :EndTrap
          :Else
              Error'Source file defines "',actnames,'", rather than "',expnames,'"'
          :EndIf
      :EndIf
      :If opts.fastLoad  ‚ćĚ do not spend time avoiding name clashes - actnc will be all 0's anyway
          mask‚Üźactncs‚ąä¬Į1   ‚ćĚ invalid names
          failed,‚Üźmask/allfiles
          (allfiles parents expnames actnames actncs)/‚ć®‚Üź‚äā~mask    ‚ćĚ keep only names that are valid
          allnames‚Üźparents JoinNames expnames  ‚ćĚ do not infer true apl name from source
      :Else
          mask‚Üźactncs‚ąä¬Į1 0    ‚ćĚ invalid names or source
          failed,‚Üź(mask‚ąßmask\1‚Č†1 ‚éēNINFO mask/allfiles)/allfiles   ‚ćĚ report invalid file names, except directories
          (allfiles parents expnames actnames actncs)/‚ć®‚Üź‚äā~mask    ‚ćĚ keep only names that are valid
          allnames‚Üźparents JoinNames actnames  ‚ćĚ fully qualified names
          :If ‚ą®/mask‚Üź(inx‚Üź‚ć≥‚ć®allnames)‚Č†(‚ć≥‚ČĘallnames)
              Error'Files produce clashing APL names:',FmtLines‚Üď‚ćē((WinSlash¬®allfiles),(‚äā'‚Üź‚Üí'),[1.5]allnames)[,(mask/inx),[1.5]‚ćłmask;]
          :EndIf
      :EndIf
     
      ‚ćĚ rename files if incorrectly named - cannot work with opts.fastLoad
      :If (0<‚ČĘallfiles)‚ąßopts.(fastLoad<forceExtensions‚ą®forceFilenames)
          expfiles‚Üź‚äÉopts(1 DetermineFileName)parents actnames actnames actncs ‚ć¨
          expfiles‚Üźexpfiles(opts.forceFilenames MergeFileName opts.forceExtensions)¬®allfiles
          :If ‚ą®/mask‚Üźexpfiles‚ČĘ¬®allfiles
              :If (‚ČĘexpfiles)‚Č†(‚ČĘ‚ą™0 CaseText expfiles)
                  Error'Forcing file names would produce clashing file names: use forceFilenames=0 or caseCode=1'
              :Else
                  ‚ćĚ because APL names don't clash, we now expfiles won't clash either
                  ‚ćĚ however expfiles may overlap allfiles, producing an error at intermediate steps (‚éēNMOVE should fail, because ‚ć†'IfExists' 'Error')
                  (mask/expfiles)Relocate(mask/allfiles)
                  allfiles‚Üźexpfiles
              :EndIf
          :EndIf
      :EndIf
     
      :If 3=‚éēNC opts.beforeRead ‚ćĚ user handler defined?
          mask‚Üź(‚ćīallfiles)‚ćī1
          :For i :In ‚ć≥‚ćīallfiles
              mask[i]‚Üź(opts‚ćéopts.beforeRead)'beforeRead'opts(i‚äÉallfiles)(i‚äÉallnames)(|i‚äÉactncs) ‚ćĚ return 1 to continue else 0
          :EndFor
          (allfiles parents expnames actnames actncs allnames)/‚ć®‚Üź‚äāmask    ‚ćĚ keep what was not processed by user
      :EndIf
     
      :Select overwrite
      :Case ¬Į1 ‚čĄ :If ~EmptyNamespace target source   ‚ćĚ target must be empty (or already linked to the matching file)
              Error'Destination namespace not empty: ',(‚ćētarget) ‚čĄ :EndIf
      :Case 0 ‚čĄ :If ‚ą®/mask‚Üź0<‚éēNC allnames~‚äā‚ćētarget   ‚ćĚ no new name must be already defined - excepted the root which may have non-imported stsuff
              Error'Names already exist: use -overwrite flag to force overwriting the following names:',FmtLines mask/allnames~‚äā‚ćētarget ‚čĄ :EndIf
      :Else ‚čĄ ‚ćĚ otherwise silently overwrite - excepted root namespace
          ‚éēEX(‚äā‚ćētarget)~‚ć®(‚Ćä|actncs){(‚ćļ‚Č†(‚Ćä|‚éēNC ‚ćĶ))/‚ćĶ}allnames  ‚ćĚ allow changing nameclass where necessary - do not expunge all to avoid issue #86
      :EndSelect
     
      (alldirs _ allexts)‚Üź‚Üď‚ćČ‚ÜĎ‚éēNPARTS allfiles
      FixFile‚Üź(FixTie opts){(target file name)‚Üź‚ćĶ ‚čĄ 0‚Č§target QFix file name ‚ćļ‚ćļ ‚ćļ 0}  ‚ćĚ ‚ćļ is force, ‚ćĶ is (target file name)
      flatten‚Üźopts.flatten
      :If ~hasnc‚Üź~opts.fastLoad  ‚ćĚ fastLoad produces (actnc‚ąä¬Į1 0) - so must rely on file extension to classify order
          actncs+‚Üź¬Į9.1√ó(allfiles‚ąäalldirs)‚ąß(actncs=0)  ‚ćĚ that's how we detect tradns/dirs - actnc=¬Į1 must remain so
      :EndIf
      ‚ćĚ fix in order: tradns, vars, fns/ops, scripted ns, interfaces, classes
      ‚ćĚ note that ‚éē*.apla is expected to remain in front because ListFiles has put them first
      ncorder‚Üź¬Į9.1 2.1 3.1 3.2 4.1 4.2 9.1 9.4 9.5  ‚ćĚ sort by actual name class (default)
      extorder‚Üźopts.typeExtensions‚ąėTail¬®ncorder     ‚ćĚ sort by file extension (fastLoad)
     
      ‚ćĚ process one directory and all its files at once - process parent before children
      todo‚Üź{‚äā‚ćĶ}‚Ćłalldirs  ‚ćĚ no need to sort because ListFiles lists parents before children
      :Repeat   ‚ćĚ keep fixing as long as at least one succeeds - we might have :Class inheristance/interfaces, :Includes, etc.
          lasttodo‚Üźtodo ‚čĄ todo‚Üź‚ć¨ ‚ćĚ first todo is a list of lists, to fix by directory, but then all remaining files are fixed in one block
          :For inx :In ‚äÜlasttodo
              (file parent expname actname actnc fullname ext)‚Üźinx‚ąė{‚ćĶ[‚ćļ]}¬®(allfiles parents expnames actnames actncs allnames allexts)
              ‚ćĚ create namespace for directory and load quadVars.apln
              :If ¬Į9.1‚ąäactnc
                  :If 1‚Č†‚ČĘ‚ą™('/'=‚äĘ/¬®file)(actnc=¬Į9.1)((‚ČĘinx)‚ÜĎ1) ‚čĄ Error'Internal error: mismatch between unscripted namespaces and directories' ‚čĄ :EndIf
                  dir‚Üź‚äÉfile ‚čĄ ns‚Üź‚äÉfullname
                  :If ~flatten            ‚ćĚ if not flattening, create nss
                      ns‚Üźns ‚éēNS ‚ć¨       ‚ćĚ preserve root namespace in case it has non-imported stuff
                      :If 0=‚ČĘns       ‚ćĚ could not create namespace
                          failed,‚Üźfile  ‚ćĚ will not attempt to fix any file in that namespace
                          :Continue
                      :EndIf
                      fixed,‚Üź‚äāns ‚čĄ fixedfiles,‚Üź‚äāfile ‚čĄ ns‚Üź‚ćéns
                  :Else
                      ns‚Üźtarget   ‚ćĚ all files fixed in target namespace
                  :EndIf
                  ‚ćĚ set sysvars before anything else - these files are produced by Acre and must be supported
                  :If ‚éēNEXISTS quadfile‚Üźdir,'quadVars.apln'
                  :AndIf ~1 FixFile ns quadfile'quadVars'
                      failed,‚Üź‚äāquadfile
                  :EndIf  ‚ćĚ successful fix is silent
                  mask‚Üź0@1‚äĘ(~file‚ąä‚äāquadfile)  ‚ćĚ ‚ćĚ directory and quadfile are done
                  (file parent expname actname actnc fullname ext inx)/‚ć®‚Üź‚äāmask
              :Else
                  :If ‚ą®/'/'=‚äĘ/¬®file ‚čĄ Error'Internal error: mismatch between unscripted namespaces and directories' ‚čĄ :EndIf
              :EndIf
              ‚ćĚ fix individual files
              :If 0‚ąä‚ćīinx ‚čĄ :Continue ‚čĄ :EndIf       ‚ćĚ no file to fix
              :If ~flatten ‚čĄ ns‚Üź‚ćé¬®parent   ‚ćĚ not flattening: use parent namespaces (not doable before the ‚éēNS above)
              :Else ‚čĄ ns‚Üźtarget                     ‚ćĚ all files fixed in target namespace
              :EndIf
              :If hasnc ‚čĄ order‚Üź‚ćčncorder‚ć≥actnc
              :Else ‚čĄ order‚Üź‚ćčextorder‚ć≥ext
              :EndIf
              mask‚Üź0 FixFile¬®(‚äāorder)‚Ć∑‚Üďns,file,[1.5]actname  ‚ćĚ do not fix with error because Classes could become uninstanciatable
              fixed,‚Üźfullname[mask/order] ‚čĄ fixedfiles,‚Üźfile[mask/order]    ‚ćĚ those fixed OK
              todo,‚Üźinx[(~mask)/order]        ‚ćĚ those failed to fix - try again at next :Repeat
          :EndFor
      :Until (‚ČĘ‚ąätodo)‚ąä0(‚ČĘ‚ąälasttodo)   ‚ćĚ all fixed or number of failures hasn't changed
      :If IS181 ‚čĄ :AndIf ~0‚ąä‚ćītodo‚Üź‚ąätodo  ‚ćĚ last attempt to fix those that failed - v18.0 cannot fix with errors
          :If ~flatten ‚čĄ ns‚Üź‚ćé¬®parents[todo]     ‚ćĚ not flattening: use parent namespaces (not doable before the ‚éēNS above)
          :Else ‚čĄ ns‚Üźtarget                     ‚ćĚ all files fixed in target namespace
          :EndIf
          mask‚Üź1 FixFile¬®‚Üďns,allfiles[todo],[1.5]actnames[todo]  ‚ćĚ attempt to fix with error - will be considered failed whether it succeeds or not
      :EndIf
      failed,‚Üźallfiles[todo]    ‚ćĚ mark as failed even if fixed with errors
      ‚ćĚfailed,‚Üźallnames[todo]     ‚ćĚ give APL name rather than file name so that user can double click on it ?
      :If ‚ą®/mask‚Üźinx‚ąä(inx‚Č†‚ć≥‚ČĘfixed)/inx‚Üź‚ć≥‚ć®fixed  ‚ćĚ should happen only if opts.fastLoad - otherwise clashes should be detected before actual fixes
          Error 1‚ÜďFmtLines(‚äā'Files produce clashing APL names:'),,/(mask/fixedfiles),(‚äā' ‚Üí '),[1.5](mask/fixed)
      :EndIf
