    ‚ąá r‚Üźlevel UCMD_Help cmd;info;Means;m;mods;myMods;myModI;myModS;a;modVals;modTxts;argTxts;myArgs;myArgI;myArgss;args;myArgS;unknown
      info‚Üź{‚ćĶ‚äÉ‚ć®‚ćĶ.Name‚ć≥‚äĘ/'.'(‚Č†‚äÜ‚äĘ)cmd}UCMD_List
     
      m‚Üź‚ćČ‚ć™'' '' ''
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-all' '' 'break all links (in all children of # and ‚éēSE)'
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-arrays' '{=name1,name2,...}' 'set to 1 to export all arrays, or set to comma-separated list of names to export a selected list of array names'
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-beforeread' '=<fn>' 'name of function to call before reading a file'
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-beforewrite' '=<fn>' 'name of function to call before writing a file'
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-casecode' '' 'add octal suffixes to preserve capitalisation on systems that ignore case'
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-codeextensions' '=<var>' 'name of vector of file extensions to be considered code'
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-create' '' 'create a configuration file if it does not exist'
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-extended' '' 'include additional properties for each link'
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-extension' '=<ext>' 'file extension of created file if different from link''s default for the nameclass'
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-fastload' '' 'reduce the load time by not inspecting source to detect name clashes'
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-flatten' '' 'merge items from all subdirectories into target directory'
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-forceextensions' '' 'rename existing files so they adhere to the type specific file extensions'
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-forcefilenames' '' 'rename existing files so their names match their contents'
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-getfilename' '=<fn>' 'name of function to call to specify a custom file name for a given APL item'
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-ignoreconfig' '' 'ignore configuration files'
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-text' '={aplan|plain}' 'always use array notation to store arrays, even if value is plain text'
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-overwrite' '' 'overwrite destination if needed'
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-proceed' '' 'perform changes required to resynchronise'
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-recursive' '={on|off|error}' 'whether children namespaces linked to their own directories must be unlinked too'
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-source' '={ns|dir|auto}' 'which source is authoritative if both are populated'
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-sysvars' '' 'Export namespace-scoped system variables to file for all unscripted namespaces'
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-typeextensions' '=<var>' 'name of two-column matrix with name classes and extensions'
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-watch' '={none|ns|dir|both}' 'which source to track for changes so the other can be synchronised'
      m‚ć™‚Üź'-recordflags' '' 'save stop and trace flags to configuration file'
      (mods modVals modTxts)‚Üź‚Üď‚ćČm
      myMods‚Üź'-\pL+'‚éēS'&'‚äĘinfo.Parse
